IDE Selection:

Choose a Python Integrated Development Environment (IDE) from the following options:
     Visual Studio Code (VS Code) or Jupyter Notebook.   
 Install the Selected IDE on your computer. 

Visual Studio Code :

Follow this link to download VS Code - https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/setup/windows

                          ( or )

Follow this Steps : 
-> Download the VS Code file from the Official Website.
-> Execute the download file.
-> Accept the Terms & Conditions.
-> Click on the Install button.
-> Wait for the installation to complete.
-> Click on the Launch button to start it.

Jupyter Notebook:

Follow this link to know how to install it - https://docs.jupyter.org/en/latest/install/notebook-classic.html

                            ( or )

For install Jupyter Notebook prior to this install Python from the official website - https://www.python.org/downloads/

We can install Jupyter Notebook through Command Prompt (cmd) and Install the classic Jupyter Notebook with:
                   "pip install notebook"

Follow this link - https://jupyter.org/install
